items.text:
# EXCITING WEEKEND AHEAD

We‚Äôre holding our final casting session for the main roles in Got to Be Certain. The shortlist is full of fantastic actors, and it‚Äôs going to be tough to make the final selections.

This project has been a joy to shape, and we can‚Äôt wait to see these performances bring the story to life. Stay tuned for updates - big things are coming!

There's still a chance to be part of this exciting project. A Casting Call is open until 31st December for some of the support roles in the film. Please see the images attached to this post. To apply, please email **doublesixproductionsltd@gmail.com** with your details and the role for which you would like to apply.

NOTE: You must be based in the North West of England, preferably Lancashire, as filming takes place in Chorley and the surrounding areas.

Follow us on instagram: [https://instagram/doublesixproductions.ig](https://instagram/doublesixproductions.ig)

Get in the mood by listening to the soundtrack on Amazon Music (no subscription required) [https://music.amazon.co.uk/user-playlists/a51a2af0e4ae4943b5b234ad97728018engb?marketplaceId=A1F83G8C2ARO7P&musicTerritory=GB&ref=dm_sh_VN1CdGRSfm1f4tWYxwk7ABpy5](https://music.amazon.co.uk/user-playlists/a51a2af0e4ae4943b5b234ad97728018engb?marketplaceId=A1F83G8C2ARO7P&musicTerritory=GB&ref=dm_sh_VN1CdGRSfm1f4tWYxwk7ABpy5)

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR LATINO OR HISPANIC PEOPLE
For upcoming Non-Union Series, ANCIENT BODIES SEASON 2.

Looking for:
 
Latino or Hispanic People, all genders and Ages, and specifically:

- 1 x Latino and Hispanic, Female, Age 20-30 with Dark Brown Hair
- 1 x Latino and Hispanic Male, Age 35-40

Non-Union Actors Only
Rate: $200 per Day Flat
Manitoba Residents Only  
MUST HAVE SIN #: Canadian Citizen or Permanent Resident or have a Valid Work Permit (No Student Permits with no SIN number)

Where: Winnipeg and the surrounding areas, Manitoba

Dates: December 11th to 12th,  December 16-19th, 2025 

Please email info@oafilmstudio.com with the subject line of the role you‚Äôre sending in for - YOUR NAME

Send the following info:
- Full Name
- Age
- Gender
- Ethnicity
- Height
- Phone
- Email Address
- State that you are non-union and a Manitoba resident 
- State if you are a Canadian Citizen, or Permanent Resident (PR), or have a Valid Work Permit? (Not a student Permit or work permit, still being processed)
- Your availability from December 11th to 12th and  December 16-19, 2025 (Must be available all day and evening)
- Confirm if you have no Tattoos or not
- Do you have your own transportation or a reliable ride?
- If you have any acting or performance experience, let us know (Speaking, SOC, Background, Theatre, Public speaking, Social Media). No experience is alright.

- 2 Current (TAKEN DAY OF SUBMISSION) Photos (1 selfie & 1 Full Body Shot)

Please share!

#Winnipeg #winnipegcastingcall #WinnipegActing

topComments.text: If you're with a legit agency for acting then they will most likely have an exclusivity clause with you, no? It's reasonably common for an actor to have a separate agency for voiceover work or for modelling, but having two agents representing you for theatre, TV, film and commercials can cause issues. How long have you been with your agent, and why do you feel you need to look elsewhere?
Spotlight has a list. I‚Äôll see if I can find it.

Topics we‚Äôre shooting:

items.text:
We're looking for 2 actors for a powerful, emotive short drama shooting in Burton upon Trent.

This project deals with intense emotional themes, so we need performers who can confidently deliver strong, nuanced screen emotion.

Male - Age 50-60

Native midlands accent. 

The father of our story. A stoic part of a man trying to hold it together after the loss of a child while trying to support his other son.

Male - Age 18-25

Native midlands accent.

The son. Lost. Hurt. Emotionally ruined after losing his brother. This character has very few lines so requires a lot of performance through facial expression and emotion.

Shoot Dates:

12th & 13th December (2-day shoot)

8am‚Äì4pm each day

Pay:

¬£250 per day including expenses

We are casting MIDLAND talent only, please be advised if you apply outside the region you will be responsible for travel and accommodation 

If you're interested, please send your headshot, showreel, and a brief introduction to me via DM (I will see requests) we are casting via showreel but will be holding a final round of auditions in Birmingham. 

Please share with anyone who may be suitable ‚Äî thank you!

dont have a showreel but this was an exaggerated version we filmed for an audition recently for my son Connerdicksonact - a version we recorded ourself for fun that actually went against all of the instructions of the brief - it turned out great and reminded us of some of the guys from Trainspotting back in the day (hence the music we put over the recording for effect) - Conner is 14 but I guess now is getting to that position were he can play above his age as really started to sprout this year. Been acting/auditioning for a few years and appeared in some movies not released yet but looking for more opportunities in TV/Film - any feedback appreciated. 

We live in Scotland but flexible to travel and have done this previously at Reading film studios.

Also has dialect training/skills in most accents in England/Ireland/USA/Eastern European/Australian.

sharedPost.text:
Last night Alternate Shadows performed at Walderslade Working Men's Club. This was our first time at the Club and it was great to see so many faces getting engrossed in the investigation! A very welcoming and warm atmosphere awaited us from John & Liz Tootell. We certainly look forward to returning again in 2026! 

The Walderslade Club (also known as the Walderslade Working Men's Club), is a member of the [CIU - the Club & Institutes Union](http://www.wmciu.org.uk/), which means that members can also access other CIU clubs around the country (after paying an additional small fee) serving the local community since 1937.

The fully air conditioned club consists of the main hall area with dance floor, and includes a large screen with Sky Sports. Next to the hall is the bar area with gaming machines, digital jukebox and TV, and then the back Sports Bar area features 4 dart boards, pool table, and two more large TVs playing Sky Sports & TNT Sports.

Our final Murder Mystery tonight is a private booking for King's School, Rochester as we shall be stepping into Panto with our Brand NEW family Pantomime `The Elves & The Shoe Maker' by Helen Bradshaw. 

Look out for details of bookings in your area soon on our WEBSITE  & FACEBOOK pages. 

For the Murder Mystery enthusiasts - don't panic we will be returning to intrigue and entertain you again from March 2026 with a brand NEW Murder Mystery written by our very own Kerrie Thompson.

We‚Äôre assembling a creative team to produce original, high-quality comedy sketches in the style of SNL, MadTV, and classic sketch shows. We‚Äôre looking for dedicated professionals and passionate creatives in the Houston area who are ready to collaborate and build something fresh.

Open Roles:

Actors/Comedians ‚Äì Strong comedic timing, improv skills a plus.

Writers/Screenwriters ‚Äì Sketch ideas, punch-up jokes, script structure.

Directors ‚Äì Oversee production, shape tone and style.

Producers ‚Äì Organize shoots, budgets, and schedules.

Crew ‚Äì Camera, sound, editing, lighting, makeup, costumes.

What We‚Äôre Building:
A recurring sketch show (shorts for YouTube, social media, and live events) based in Houston. Think fast-paced, topical comedy, character pieces, and original concepts.

Actors friends! I have a 1-day shoot paid opportunity for non-union talent. Shoot is on Aug 20th (half to potentially full day) in Burbank, CA. (Content will live on social media in perpetuity.)

Details below and submit to: B.wagner03@gmail.com

We're casting "real people" or talent as real people who have had corporate 9-5 work experience even in unique industries. The project is tentatively titled, "Generational Divide," and it is a docu-style shoot that features folks of different generations sharing their POVs on professionalism and workplace culture. The goal is to spark meaningful conversation with real and even humorous takes on common or expected work experiences, amongst a group of people in a relaxed environment.

If interested, please submit a headshot, any social links, and a super casual self-tape** (1-2 min): **Help us get to know you! Name, age, current or past ‚Äú9‚Äì5‚Äù job, plus anything that makes you, you (hobbies, etc.). Then, answer 2 of the following questions (no right answers :):

- What‚Äôs the weirdest or outdated office policy you‚Äôve seen?
- What‚Äôs an unspoken rule of office culture you live by?
- How do you feel about being ‚Äòalways on‚Äô or reachable?
- What does your generation get right/wrong about work?
- What‚Äôs one generational work stereotype you love/hate? 
*Email attachments or Google drive links are accepted.

items.text:
I'm 15 and wondering if anyone knows were I can find casting calls for my age, I have been doing theatre performances since I was 10 and want to make the step into film and TV

thank you in advance

topComments.text:
Unless you look very young, casting directors will  usually go for a recent young looking  grad to play age 15. 
It's nearly gcse year  for you so I would pause your acting and really  concentrate on your exams because you will defo need a side hustle to pay the bills even if you do well in the industry. 
Get good gcses and A levels  (avoid Arts  A levels which are notoriously hard to get top marks and can be very frustrating if others in the group are not as committed!) to keep all options open for your future.

**ROLES AVAILABLE**

*Female Presenting | 18‚Äì25*

*Male Presenting | 40s‚Äì50s*
Worn down by years under an oppressive regime. Emotionally numb but deeply devoted to giving his daughter the freedom he never had.

Den Alltag eines Ehepaares nach vielen gemeinsamen Beziehungsjahren bringt uns Neele Leana Vollmar empathisch auf die Leinwand. So nebenbei durften wir auch mit der Regisseurin ein paar Worte wechseln.

‚ÄòThe Lines We Crossed‚Äô short film üé¨

A raw and tender story of found family, the messiness of healing, and the unexpected power of being seen. Three lives, stitched together by loneliness, come alive in the light of connection - and in that light, hope can take root where none was meant to grow.

Secondary role: 
Mrs. Kane is dramatic, flirty, and unapologetically over-the-top, with a flair for gossip and a love of all things a little chavvy. While she loves both of her children, her eldest, Cody, is clearly the favorite - her pride and joy - often leaving Keira to fend for herself. Mrs. Kane desperately clings to Cody‚Äôs success, seeing it as her ticket to status and financial security.

‚Ä¢ Female
‚Ä¢ 30-55 years
‚Ä¢ White/Caucasian
‚Ä¢ Brunette/ Redhead/ Auburn hair
‚Ä¢ London Accent

üìçLocation: London
üóìÔ∏è Dates: 6/12/25
üí∞ Payment: Unpaid

To audition please contact @lines_we_crossed_film on instagram or send Madeleine Bloore a message here on Facebook.

**Hi everyone!**
I'm casting for a *student stage reading* of an original play at Rider University.

We are looking for:
* **One actor to read for the main character**, a 14-year-old boy
* **An actor for the role of the Father**
* **An actor for the role of the Policeman**
* **And a few supporting female roles**

If you're interested, please fill out this form for more details and to apply.

https://forms.gle/HKyELuh6ko6vUGdr5
DM me if you have any questions!

items.text:
Location: Either near Irvine, CA or Ontario, CA
Shoot Dates: December 3, 4, or 5
Time Commitment/Shoot Length: 3-4 Hours 
Compensation: $100 flat for 3‚Äì4 hours + a meals or snacks/drinks 

Project Type: I‚Äôm a sports medicine/orthopedic professional, not a filmmaker, but I‚Äôve been tasked with producing an updated educational video for use in college classrooms. I‚Äôm looking for an outgoing, open-minded, athletic female model/actress (18‚Äì30) to participate in this short film that illustrates the accessibility and mobility challenges someone experiences during a temporary leg injury. All equipment (crutches, splint/cast) is provided. The cast is non-permanent and applied/removed safely.

About the Role:
You‚Äôll portray someone recovering from a short-term lower-limb injury while navigating everyday environments‚Äîstores, stairs, hallways, buildings‚Äîusing crutches and a removable cast/splint. The filming will take place over 3‚Äì4 hours in one day and will be edited to appear as multiple days. You will be responsible for your own makeup/wardrobe but we can discuss what is expected!

Creative Collaboration:
Because I‚Äôm approaching this from a healthcare perspective rather than a filmmaking one, I welcome creative input and collaboration. If you have ideas, insights, or personal experience that could make the scenes more realistic or engaging, I‚Äôm very open to incorporating them.

Who I‚Äôm Looking For:
Female, 18‚Äì30
Athletic, active, or fitness-oriented
Comfortable with walking non weight bearing on crutches
Good on camera and able to portray authentic emotion (pain, irritation, joy, etc.)
Able to bring a few outfit options and personal items (e.g., backpack, different outfits)
Acting/modeling experience not required
Experience with crutches or prior injuries is a plus
Based in Southern California

Project Details
Amateur, non-union
Educational, documentary-style
Mostly improvised with some guidance
Small, supportive, low-pressure environment
Opportunity to contribute creatively

To Apply
Please DM me, comment below, or email brettsmithh316@gmail.com with:
Your name + age
Headshot and full-body photo
A short intro about you addressing relative experience (video recording preferred)
Relevant experience (acting, sports, crutches/cast experience)
Your availability Dec 3, 4, or 5

Thanks!

items.text:
üö© RED FLAGS TO WATCH OUT FOR When Choosing a Talent Agency! üö©

If you‚Äôre an actor, model, or creator looking for real opportunities, make sure you protect yourself and your career. Here are some major red flags that should make you RUN, not walk:

üî¥ They ask for high upfront fees
Legit agencies make money when you make money  not before.

üî¥ No real clients or bookings to show
If they can‚Äôt show actual work, partnerships, or success stories, be careful.

üî¥ They pressure you to sign on the spot
A professional agency gives you time to read the contract and think it through.

üî¥ They demand you use their photographer only
Training and photos are optional, not required. You should never be forced.

üî¥ They offer guaranteed fame
No one can promise bookings. Real agencies guide you  they don‚Äôt sell dreams.

üî¥ Lack of communication or transparency
Unanswered emails, vague answers, and unclear expectations? üö©üö©üö©

üî¥ They take your money but don‚Äôt work for you
If they aren‚Äôt submitting you, promoting you, or supporting you, that‚Äôs a problem.

topComments.text: Yes on all of the above! And a manager and/or agent should provide a submission report to prove they are submitting you. NEVER pay to play! üíØ

Sounds like 2010 thinking.

What are agents even booking anymore?  Gatekeepers running out of gates to keep, lol.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL FOR A 10-MIN SHORT FILM**
Hi everyone! We‚Äôre seeking local actors for a neorealist short film shooting in late January in Vancouver. The film is intended for 2026 festival submissions.

**Logline:**

A college student volunteers on a visual-assist app to help an elderly man in his small apartment, unaware that a quiet glitch has turned their private calls into a public stream.

**Production Details**

‚Ä¢ Location: Vancouver, BC

‚Ä¢ Shoot Window: Late January ‚Äì Early February 2026 (TBD)

‚Ä¢ Genre: Neorealist Drama

‚Ä¢ Non-Union / Volunteer

‚Ä¢ Meals + IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**MAYA ‚Äî Female, 19‚Äì24 (Open Ethnicity)**

Quiet, inward, emotionally guarded.
Minimal dialogue; performance driven by micro-reactions and natural handheld close-ups.
Must be comfortable with subtle, restrained acting.
Grounded student under stress ‚Äî *Wendy & Lucy*, *Never Rarely Sometimes Always* tone.

**LEON ‚Äî Male, 65‚Äì80 (Open Ethnicity)**

Soft-spoken, solitary, dignified.
Partially visually impaired; actor need not be visually impaired but must portray limited vision naturally.
Understated physicality: small gestures, hesitation, lived-in presence.

**TO APPLY**

Please send the following to **seetogetherfilm@gmail.com**
Subject: **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì MAYA‚Äù** or **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì LEON‚Äù**
‚Ä¢ Recent headshot
‚Ä¢ Short introduction (video or written)
‚Ä¢ Availability (Jan‚ÄìFeb 2026)
‚Ä¢ Any naturalistic acting samples (if available)

We will cast people first through self-tapes.

Thank you!

Partially visually impaired; actor need not be visually impaired but must portray limited vision naturally.
Understated physicality: small gestures, hesitation, lived-in presence.

Subject: **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì MAYA‚Äù** or **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì LEON‚Äù**
‚Ä¢ Recent headshot

‚Ä¢ Availability (Jan‚ÄìFeb 2026)

We will cast people first through self-tapes.

Thank you!
items.title: **CASTING CALL FOR A 10-MIN SHORT FILM**

items.text:
LOGLINE: 

In a distant future, Callie Jones works as a hacker whose illegal activities draw the attention of the future's police force, potentially endangering their budding romance and their freedom.

WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

Faye (she/her, trans-femme, 25-30) - Faye is an aspiring fashion designer and a close friend/ love interest to Callie. She is a gentle person who has plenty of love for anyone she meets, though even her patience has its limits. Years of living paycheque to paycheque in an unforgiving capitalist dystopia have her yearning for a stable life where she can be free to create and to love freely.

Shooting dates: Dec 1st, 2nd, 13th, 14th

Non union, paid work ($100 per day, open to negotiation), lunch provided.

Please send a headshot, resume, and demo reel (if applicable) to iamkarlyelyse@gmail.com

üé• Film: Blackbird | Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs Fan Film
üì¢ LAST CALL ‚Äì Letzte M√∂glichkeit, sich zu melden!
‚è∞ Wann?
10.01.2026
Eine √úbernachtung am 10.01. ist selbstverst√§ndlich m√∂glich.
üí∏ Gage: 100 ‚Ç¨
‚ùó Fahrtkosten und Verpflegung sind nicht enthalten, da das Projekt komplett privat finanziert wird.
Die √úbernachtung wird jedoch √ºbernommen.
üìç Wo?
N√∂rdlingen, Landkreis Donau-Ries
üé≠ Wer?
Rolle: Sam (3 Szenen)
Gesucht wird eine Schauspielerin (18‚Äì35 Jahre) mit sehr gutem oder akzentfreiem Englisch und einem jugendlichen Erscheinungsbild (die Charaktere sind Teenager).
Idealerweise mit F√ºhrerschein, da ich leider schlechte Erfahrungen mit Drehtagen und Bahnverbindungen gemacht habe. Falls es anders nicht geht, kann ich mir dar√ºber noch Gedanken machen.
üßç‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Kurzbeschreibung der Rolle ‚ÄûSam‚Äú:
Sam ist ein ganz normales, freundliches Teenager-M√§dchen, das viel lacht, offen ist und es liebt, in die Kamera zu sprechen.
üé¨ Kurze Beschreibung zum Projekt:
Nole und Sam m√ºssen f√ºr ein Schulprojekt einen Kurzfilm drehen. Doch das Kost√ºm von Blackbird erwacht zum Leben und beginnt, die beiden gnadenlos zu verfolgen.
Der Film wird auch im Lost-&-Found-Footage-Stil gedreht.
üí° √úber mich:
Ich bin ein noch sehr unerfahrener, fast schon amateurhafter Filmemacher und habe bisher vier kurze Filme auf meinem YouTube-Kanal ver√∂ffentlicht.
Wenn ihr nach gro√üen Projekten f√ºr euer Portfolio sucht, ist das hier vermutlich nicht das Richtige.
Das Drehbuch ist bereits fertig und ich zeige es euch gerne bei Interesse.

Da es um Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs geht und die Fanbase sehr gro√ü ist, hoffe ich dennoch, dass der Film viele Klicks bekommen wird ‚Äì es bleibt aber klar ein Hobbyprojekt.
Der fertige Film wird auf YouTube ver√∂ffentlicht.

üëâ Ich freue mich sehr auf eure Nachrichten! üòÉ

items.text:
## **Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

‚ÄúWhen a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma‚Äô

**üéì Lead Roles**

**AMAIA**

**Female | Playing age: 20-30 | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A young woman, grief-stricken, haunted by a recent miscarriage. Intelligent, emotionally complex, volatile, and deeply human. Fluctuates between tender vulnerability and violent dissociation.

 **Performance notes:** Requires a wide emotional range ‚Äî subtle detachment, raw grief, moments of horror, as well as serenity towards the end.  Appears in nearly every scene.

 **Comparable roles:** Charlotte Gainsbourg (*Antichrist*), Essie Davis (*The Babadook*), Jennifer Connelly *(Requiem for a Dream), *Isabelle Adjani *(Possession)*

This is a dual-role as they will also be playing the character of Amaia‚Äôs Doppelganger

**AMAIA'S DOPPELGANGER **

**Female | Same actor as Amaia preferred**

 **Description:** An uncanny mirror of Amaia ‚Äî at times gentle, at times mocking or malevolent. Not a "villain" but an emotional specter. She represents Amaia‚Äôs true opinion of herself, and pulls at her mental fragility to attempt to make her finally give in to her pain.

 **Performance notes:** If dual casting is not possible, physical resemblance and matched acting style are key. The role is symbolic and dreamlike.

 **Type:** Similar movement to Amaia, but with a more ‚Äòfloaty‚Äô and ethereal feel to it.

The nature of a dual role would suit an actress who really wants a challenge - as well as the maximum amount of screen time for any character in the film. Hopefully, a brilliant showcase role for talent who want to establish themselves as a critically respected performer, as they will be carrying the vast bulk of the film‚Äôs emotional core.

We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with three scenes needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require ten days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia‚Äôs partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia‚Äôs. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**üë• Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events ‚Äî a mythic observer of Amaia‚Äôs trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

items.text:
# **Casting Call ‚Äî Student Film**

****UPDATE: Thank you so much to everyone who has sent in a showreel. Due to the amount of applications we have received, we've made the difficult decision to close the applications early. Therefore, any applications received after midnight on *****Sun 30th Nov***** will unfortunately not be able to be considered.****

**Currently casting for a student final project film, shooting in January-February 2026.**

We‚Äôre currently looking for three actors for a student short film: two male (playing age 18-24) and one female (playing age 18-24).

No other physical features required, so open to all.

Please send showreel links and recent headshots to **casting@desktopstudios.co.uk** ‚Äî along with any other additional materials you want us to see.

Closing date is December 5th, as shooting begins in the new year. Must live near or be happy to travel to London among various locations, with travel and food fully covered.

## More Information

**Synopsis**

When Elias, a forlorn cinema clerk, encounters a mysterious figure who claims to know him, the pair embark on an emotional odyssey through memory and illusion. As the line between past and present fractures, and the distinction between the real and the surreal becomes ever-more blurred, Elias must confront the truths he‚Äôs long avoided ‚Äî and the self he‚Äôs tried to forget.

**Character overview: ELIAS**

Male, early 20s. Elias works in a cinema, struggling to come to terms with a recent emotional loss. He is slightly self-pitying, but becomes a serious, grounded character by the end.

**Character overview: LUCID**

Male, early 20s. Lucid is Elias‚Äô emotional foil: extroverted, while compassionate and mysterious.

**Character overview: ISOBELLA**

Female, early 20s. She is Elias‚Äô recent emotional loss. The whole story revolves around her, but she has minimal actual dialogue. She is a bit of a closed book, and could be played in a few ways.

**Shooting Dates**

Shooting dates to be confirmed, but will be between January and February 2026. Must be available within that window, but dates will be decided based on cast and crew availability within this time.

**Shooting Locations**

Various, including Kent, Buckinghamshire, and London.

**Expenses**

Travel and food will be provided, along with accommodation if necessary.

**Contact us**

To register your interest, please email **casting@desktopstudios.co.uk**. Please include any relevant information and links, such as showreels, headshots, and/or previous experience. No previous experience is required, but you must be able to showcase your abilities.

Label: Eigenlabel
Release: 21.10.2025

Benedictus quasi Deus' Interpretation von ‚ÄûOut of the dark‚Äú, das ein Falco Cover ist, ist recht ansprechend konzipiert, aber bisher nur als Youtube-Video verf√ºgbar. Der Musiker beginnt mit sanften Panfl√∂tent√∂nen und sein Gesang kommt anfangs sehr leise her√ºber. Dieses verst√§rkt die sehr innige Haltung. Sp√§ter werden die Vocals rauer. Man kann also von einem Break sprechen. Energetische Effekte bringen einen besonderen und starken Touch hinein. 

Ein starker Bass verleiht dem Song einen rockigen Flair und das vorliegende Cover ist sehr interessant aufgebaut. Falcos Grundmelodie ist zu erkennen und Benedictus quasi Deus verfremdet das Original, so dass ich es als eine sehr gute Interpretation bezeichnen kann.  

Positiv herauszustellen ist auch in der Videodarstellung der Gebrauch von einer Kerze, Explosionen und Feuer, die ein dynamisches Ambiente hervorrufen.

Youtube-Video: https://youtu.be/gfvWL6h4GKk?si=YR5U2x_QCoWfQUfy

Roman Golub 
Northern Art Music - Bodystyler Musikmagazin

üé¨** Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes: WORLDWIDE CASTING CALL **üáµüá≠

We are urgently seeking **experienced male actors (ages 31-49)** for the upcoming project, **"Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes"**! Filming will take place in the **Philippines**.

We are specifically targeting actors who hold **German, British, Czech, or American** citizenship/nationality.

**Project & Role Details**

* **Project Title:** Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes
* **IMDb Link:** [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt38781319/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0_tt_8_nm_0_in_0_q_bad%2520at%2520hellos](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt38781319/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0_tt_8_nm_0_in_0_q_bad%2520at%2520hellos)
* **Filming Location:** **Philippines** (Applicants must be willing and able to travel and work in the Philippines).
* **Compensation:** **$5,000 - $7,000 USD**, based on professional credits and experience.
* **Filming dates: **February 2026 - April 2026

**Mandatory Requirements**

* **Gender/Age:** Male, strictly **31 to 49 years old**.
* **Nationality:** Must be a citizen of **Germany, the United Kingdom, the Czech Republic, or the United States**.
* **Professional Profile:** Must have an established **IMDb Profile** with verifiable credits.
* **Social Media:** Must have a minimum of **5,000+ followers** across primary social media platform(s).

**Submission Instructions**

To be considered, please email your full submission package to:

üìß **[badathellosworseatgoodbyes@gmail.com](mailto:badathellosworseatgoodbyes@gmail.com)**

**Subject Line MUST BE:** **"CASTING SUBMISSION: MALE [YOUR AGE] - [NATIONALITY] - [YOUR NAME]"**

**Your submission package must include:**
* Professional Headshot(s) and Acting Resume/CV (attached).
* A link to your Acting Reel or recent work samples.
* A direct link to your verifiable **IMDb Profile**.
* Link(s) to your main Social Media profile(s), clearly stating your current follower count.
* Your current City and Country of residence (and where you currently hold citizenship).

üö®** DEADLINE FOR SUBMISSIONS**

All materials must be received no later than **November 26th or 27th, 2025**.

*Only selected candidates meeting ****ALL**** mandatory requirements will be contacted for auditions.*

Hello All,
We are looking for an **actor for creative UGC** (User-Generated Content) to produce engaging, relatable, and authentic video content for Helmit, a parental control app designed to protect children from harassment, predators, and cyberbullying online. Our AI analyzes social media activity privately on the device and alerts parents only when there is a potential threat. Our mission is to educate families about online safety, cyberbullying, and protecting kids in the digital world.

**Who We Are Looking For**

- Parent, preferably female, age 35 or above

- English speaking preferred, German possible as well

- Comfortable speaking on camera

- Able to create warm, natural, storytelling style content

- A parent who understands real challenges in raising kids today

- Being a parent would be perfect, but not absolutely necessary

- Ideally located in Munich or the surrounding area

- 1 day of filming

**Topics include**

- Parenting education

- Parenting stories and experiences

- Light, natural mentions of our app when relevant

- scripts will be provided by us

- You may adjust the script wording to match your tone, voice, and natural speaking style

- You do not need to involve your kids. We want great parents to be part of the project, not the children

All content will be posted by our team on Helmit‚Äôs various social media channels

**What We Value**

Our main goal is to work closely with parents so we can better understand real challenges, create relatable educational content, and continue building our product to support families more effectively.

**Application - **Please include

- Samples of your previous video work

- A brief introduction about yourself and your parenting experience

If you love storytelling, creating honest content, and want to help build a safer digital world for kids, we would love to work with you. Please contact via email: [Niklas@helmit.org](mailto:Niklas@helmit.org)

More information about us: [www.helmit.org](http://www.helmit.org)
